Also reasons why not:

>Blackmail
Killed by every government at once, who are much better at espionage than you. Who are you even going to blackmail with this? Why?

>Money hungry
Industry takes industry to function. Subina could tell us every detail of how her society produces every piece of technology they have, which she isn't going to know anyway, but we still wouldn't be able to just run off and produce it. If every Apple engineer, designer, and employee lived in 1700 they wouldn't be able to build an iPhone.

If you're going to outsmart the AI working for a species' highest ranking military officer and convince it to feed us technology, one of two things happen. It's programmed well enough to just say no, or it's programmed badly and psychologically fucks you without technically causing any harm: http://lesswrong.com/lw/1pz/the_ai_in_a_box_boxes_you/ .

>Military supremacy
This is the plot of I Have No Mouth And I Must Scream, and it's not an unrealistic one by our modern understanding of AI. Also see above.
